contents.desc: Let's make us a Tater Tot Taco Casserole! Recipe Below!
1. Preheat oven to 425¬∞ and bake tater tots for 20-25 minutes, then sprinkle with seasoned salt.
2. Dice onion and add to 2lbs of ground beef in a frying pan. Brown meat until fully cooked and onions are soft. Drain and add back to pan.
3. Add taco seasoning and water to the meat and mix over medium-high heat until most of the liquid evaporates.
4. Stir in hot diced green chilies.

5. Cube up melt and dip in a microwave safe bowl and pour the milk in. Microwave in 30 second increments, stiring every 30 seconds, until the mixture is smooth. Then add mushroom soup and mix until smooth.
6. Spread half the tater tots in the bottom of a 4 quart baking dish. Spread taco meat evenly over top, then pour the cheese mixture in an even layer over the meat.
7. Top with the remaining tater tots then sprinkle with shredded cheese.
10. Plate the tater tot casserole then top with lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream, and taco sauce.

itemList.desc: Let's make us a Tater Tot Taco Casserole! Recipe Below! #tatertot #taco #casserole #recipe #easyrecipe #homecooking #dinner #dinnerideas #southern #cooking  Tater Tot Taco Casserole: 2.5 lbs Tater Tots Seasoned Salt 2lbs Ground Beef 1 Diced Medium Onion 2 Packets Taco Seasoning 1 Cup Water 4oz Hot Green Chillies 16oz Velveeta 3/4 Cup Whole Milk 10.5 oz Can Cream of Mushroom 1.5 Cups Sharp Cheddar Lettuce Tomato Sour Cream Taco Sauce. Directions: 1. Preheat oven to 425¬∞ and bake tater tots for 20-25 minutes, then sprinkle with seasoned salt. 2. Dice onion and add to 2lbs of ground beef in a frying pan. Brown meat until fully cooked and onions are soft. Drain and add back to pan. 3. Add taco seasoning and water to the meat and mix over medium-high heat until most of the liquid evaporates. 4. Stir in hot diced green chilies. 5. Cube up melt and dip in a microwave safe bowl and pour the milk in. Microwave in 30 second increments, stiring every 30 seconds, until the mixture is smooth. Then add mushroom soup and mix until smooth. 6. Spread half the tater tots in the bottom of a 4 quart baking dish. Spread taco meat evenly over top, then pour the cheese mixture in an even layer over the meat.  7. Top with the remaining tater tots then sprinkle with shredded cheese. 8. Bake at 375¬∞ for 25 minutes. 9. Let set for 15 minutes. 10. Plate the tater tot casserole then top with lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream, and taco sauce. 11. Enjoy Huney!
